</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>ACR98:v99#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="ACR98"/><meta name="dc:title" content="ACR &#xA;              98-&#xA;                INTRODUCED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Concurrent Resolution
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 98</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Members Gallagher and Ellis<br/>(Coauthors: Assembly Members Castillo, DeMaio, Dixon, Patterson, Sanchez, and Tangipa)<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>June 12, 2025</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to law enforcement. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">ACR 98, as introduced, Gallagher.
                          Law enforcement: immigration actions.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would, among other things, call for an immediate end to policies that obstruct lawful immigration enforcement and urge the Governor to take immediate action to restore law and order.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_EE1E5412-3BF3-4C82-859B-376588C089BA"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, On Friday, June 6, 2025, federal law enforcement officers were violently attacked while carrying out lawful immigration enforcement operations in the City of Los Angeles; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_600A6DF0-43EE-4102-8D79-BAF0F29D36D8"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Those officers were met with mobs of agitators who physically obstructed lawful actions and incited chaos in the streets; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_83962FAC-D718-4B2F-A992-EB2933B2127C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Governor Gavin Newsom has refused to restore order in the City of Los Angeles, choosing instead to place blame on federal actions and on his political opponents rather than take accountability for California’s failed policies; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_F085FC8E-58BA-4276-8EA0-FCA09C90BCE0"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The violent resistance to lawful federal enforcement operations is a direct result of California’s radical sanctuary state policies which specifically restrict cooperation between state, local, and federal agencies on immigration enforcement, forcing federal authorities to conduct immigration enforcement operations directly within local communities, thereby increasing tensions and risks to public safety; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_4F605281-1DB8-47E1-B262-41D49E1F1B8B"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, These policies have created dangerous gaps in communication and coordination between agencies, making it harder to plan safe operations and emboldening those who oppose immigration enforcement to interfere without consequence; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_070DDBD9-7836-4701-8C36-EDC074D43B8A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The lawlessness witnessed in the City of Los Angeles is not an isolated incident but a predictable outcome of state policies that undermine enforcement and handcuff law enforcement; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_5A821CA3-1CBD-48A5-A65C-A7EE470D9CF2"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, the Senate thereof concurring, That the Legislature condemns the violent attacks on law enforcement officers in the City of Los Angeles and calls for an immediate end to policies that obstruct lawful immigration enforcement; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_AECD4F1E-6055-4E64-8D2D-D69F43204C77"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Legislature urges Governor Gavin Newsom to take immediate action to restore law and order, and to support full cooperation between federal, state, and local law enforcement agencies.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
